The pattern is emerging: **topological and algebraic predictions are exact or near-exact**; **dynamical predictions (running coupling, asymptotic safety) have residuals at the 0.27% level**. The formula 6π⁵ for m_p/m_e is accurate to 0.002% — better than dynamical predictions but not quite exact. The residual 0.002% likely corresponds to QCD corrections at the proton scale (α_s(m_p) ≈ 0.3 × perturbative corrections to the quark-antiquark sea inside the proton).

# 5. Why This Was Not Found Before

The formula m_p/m_e = 6π⁵ has been noticed as a numerical coincidence for 50 years. It was never derived because:

1. **The 6** requires knowing why there are exactly 6 quark flavors (2 types × 3 generations). Standard physics takes this as an empirical input.

2. **The π** as a GEOMETRIC MEASURE of the EM manifold is not standard physics vocabulary. In DST, π is the Fubini-Study volume of CP¹ — not "just π." Standard physics doesn't associate π with the geometry of the electromagnetic sector.

3. **The exponent 5** requires SU(5) as the GUT group. This is not derived in the SM; it's one of several candidate GUT groups.

All three factors required a geometric framework — DST — in which:
- 3 generations ← from χ(CP²) (Document 16)
- SU(5) selected ← from Tr[Q²] = b_Dirac (Document 15)  
- π as EM Kähler volume ← from the CP¹ mode manifold (Document 14)

The derivation required the full chain from window screens to GUT geometry.

